Buenaventura, Falabella, Renova: Latin America Equity Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-03-04T06:39:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/buenaventura-falabella-renova-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The MSCI Latin America Index rose for the fifth time in six
days, advancing 1.2 percent to 4,536.81.  Brazil    Renova Energia SA (RNEW11)  (RNEW11 BS): The Brazilian developer of
wind and hydroelectric power approved the issue of 150 million
reais ($91 million) in commercial promissory notes, according to
a regulatory filing. The shares were unchanged at 30.90 reais.    Chile     SACI Falabella (FALAB)  : Chile’s largest retailer by
market value replaced mall operator  Parque Arauco SA (PARAUCO)  in
Corpbanca’s list of five recommended Chilean stocks, the bank’s
brokerage unit wrote in an e-mailed note to clients. The shares
climbed 1.8 percent to 4,375.90 pesos. Parque Arauco (PARAUCO CC)
advanced 1.8 percent to 956.52 pesos.    Mexico   Cia. Mexicana de Aviacion said it initiated talks with
several new investor groups interested in restarting the
bankrupt airline, according to an e-mailed statement.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB (ASURB MM): The
operator of airports in southern Mexico climbed 1.8 percent to
66.15 pesos.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Pacifico SAB (GAPB MM): The
operator of airports in the Pacific and central regions of
Mexico rose 2.4 percent to 47.03 pesos.    Peru   Miners: Fifteen of 17 traders, investors and analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg, or 88 percent, said gold will rise next
week. Two predicted lower prices.    Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, fell 1.3 percent to $1.50.  Rio Alto Mining
Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company, was
unchanged at $2.41. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the
country’s biggest precious-metals miner, slumped 3.3 percent to
$45.50. Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAI1 PE), a unit of Gold
Fields Ltd., was unchanged at 3.38 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
